 -- Brian O'Reilly <fade@deepsky.com>  Thu, 04 Jun 2026 14:00:00 +0000

dsmr-localfirst (1.0-2) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Add localfirst-backend-monitor, an out-of-band vpopmail SQL backend
    liveness check run every 5 minutes from /etc/cron.d/dsmr-localfirst.  It
    emails root/postmaster once when the backend goes down (recipients are
    deferring) and once when it recovers, rather than alerting per deferred
    message, which would only worsen a degraded MTA.  No-op on hosts with no
    vpopmail backend.

 -- Brian O'Reilly <fade@deepsky.com>  Thu, 04 Jun 2026 13:00:00 +0000

dsmr-localfirst (1.0-1) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Initial release.  System-first recipient routing for hybrid system/vpopmail
    mail domains: a shared eligibility predicate (system-identity), an SMTP-time
    RCPTCHECK validator (localfirst-rcptcheck) that replaces chkuser, and a
    delivery-time .qmail-default dispatcher (localfirst-dispatch).
  * Validator defers (451) rather than rejects when the vpopmail SQL backend is
    unreachable, logging LOG_CRIT for out-of-band alerting; treats an absent
    vrcptcheck as a system-only host (unknown local recipient rejected); honours
    leading-dot rcpthosts wildcards; and chains to the next RCPTCHECK program
    (the outbound throttle) on accept.

 -- Brian O'Reilly <fade@deepsky.com>  Thu, 04 Jun 2026 12:00:00 +0000
